WILLIAM SMITH . I was formerly a detective officer, but I am now retired—I produce a certificate—(Read; "Central Criminal Court, July, 1856;
Oscar Kingston convicted of burglary and stealing 566l. 6s. 8d.
—Sentence, Five Years' Penal Servitude.")—The prisoner is the man there described as Oscar Kingston—that was a robbery at the Great Northern Hotel—I had the conduct of the case.
